text: Ok overall their wanton charsiew noodles was really good, but if you see the charsiew closely, there is a huge layer of fat, white unrendered fat taking up about 50% of the slice, so it was quite unpleasant, but the wanton was good, duck was good, sauce combination was good, their dumplings has prawn in them, so overall 4 stars, would have been 5 if their charsiew was of a different cut
I live 3 streets away and this is my go-to place when I wanna eat crispy roasted pork. Their sauce and chili is delicious too and I love eating here.
The herbal duck meat is juicy, not dry or tough. The chilli is really good and they are generous in giving a big portion. Price is reasonable.
